

ðŸ§¿ this 
 - this is keyword in java
 - this is reference variable 
 - using this to access instance variables 
 - in java this is special keyword   that refres to the current object 

ðŸ§¿ why use this 
 - refer to the current class's variables 
 _ call current class's methods 
 - call one constructor from another constructr
 - return current object 

------------------------------------
ðŸ‘‰ðŸ‘‰ All uses of this keyword 
 
1) this refers to the instances variable 
 - sometimes, local variable and     instances variable have same . so we     use this to avoide confusion
  
* instance variable 
 - it's a variable declared inside the class but outside any methods 

* local variable 
 - it's a variable declared inside a  method, constructr or block

------------------------------------

2) this to call current class method 
 - you can use this.methodName() to call another methods in the same class

class Example 
{
 void show()
  {
    System.out.println("show method");
  }
  
void disp()
 {
   this.show();
 }
public static void main (String abc[])
{
 Example ob=new Example();
 ob.disp();
 }
}

------------------------------------

3) this() to call another constructr
  
class book
{ 
 int page;
 String title;
 
 book()
 {
  this(100,"java basic");
 } 
book(int page,String title)
 {
  this.page=page;
  this.title=title;
 }
void show()
{
  System.out.println(title+" "+ page+" pages");
}
main method()
{
  book b=new book();
  b.show();
}
}
